WEBVTT

00:06:29.000 --> 00:06:31.640
until I came across this language.

00:06:32.560 --> 00:06:35.056
AG: Most people think
about introversion-extraversion

00:06:35.080 --> 00:06:37.176
as where you get your energy,

00:06:37.200 --> 00:06:39.376
like extraverts get it from people,

00:06:39.400 --> 00:06:41.080
introverts get it from being alone.

00:06:41.760 --> 00:06:43.456
But when Susan studied the science,

00:06:43.480 --> 00:06:45.976
she learned that wasn't quite right.

00:06:46.000 --> 00:06:48.816
SC: Everybody, whether you're
an introvert or an extravert,

00:06:48.840 --> 00:06:51.896
draws energy from other people

00:06:51.920 --> 00:06:55.016
and I think that we don't make
enough distinction

00:06:55.040 --> 00:06:59.376
between how many people
and in what kind of setting.

00:06:59.400 --> 00:07:02.536
There ends up being this idea,
oh, introverts are antisocial,